Item 8.01 Other Events
     On November 20, 2006, Akamai Technologies, Inc., a Delaware corporation ("Akamai"), announced that it had entered into an Agreement and Plan of Merger dated November 17, 2006 (the "Merger Agreement") by and among Akamai, Nantucket Acquisition Corp., a Delaware corporation and a wholly-owned subsidiary of Akamai, Nine Systems Corporation, a Delaware corporation ("Nine Systems"), and the principal stockholders of Nine Systems. Under the Merger Agreement, Akamai will acquire all of the outstanding equity of Nine Systems in exchange for approximately 3.1 million shares of Akamai's common stock and approximately $7 million in cash, subject to certain closing adjustments. The closing of the merger is subject to customary closing conditions including obtaining the approval of Nine Systems' stockholders.
