"Revenue" shall mean the Company's cumulative annual revenue for fiscal years 2011, 2012 and 2013 calculated in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles in the United States of America as reported in the 2013 Financial Statements.
"Normalized EPS" shall mean the Company's cumulative annual earnings per diluted share for fiscal years 2011, 2012 and 2013 excluding cumulative amortization of intangible assets, stock-based compensation, amortization of capitalized stock-based compensation, restructuring charges and benefits, acquisition-related costs, certain gains and losses on equity investments, loss on early extinguishment of debt and other items excluded by the Company when publicly reporting such metric at the time of the 2013 Reporting Date.
